WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:01.900
Dr. Masters:
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>masters of sex...</i>

00:01.902 --> 00:05.871
Because I wasn't sure
when I'd be starting
at memorial,

00:05.873 --> 00:06.739
I haven't yet told lillian.

00:06.741 --> 00:11.944
Greathouse feels
it may not be possible
for you to come to memorial.

00:11.946 --> 00:12.611
Great to see you, bill.

00:12.613 --> 00:14.213
I hope you're
treating him right,
barbara.

00:14.215 --> 00:17.282
Because he's got
a bigger following
than  <i>gunsmoke.</i>

00:17.284 --> 00:19.585
You, my dear,
are not married
to a saint.

00:19.587 --> 00:22.554
You are to keep 100 miles
away from that study.

00:22.556 --> 00:24.023
Unofficially,
I'm very interested

00:24.025 --> 00:26.859
In what happens
behind closed doors.

00:26.861 --> 00:27.693
Very, very interested.

00:27.695 --> 00:30.029
Metastasis was
always a possibility.

00:30.031 --> 00:31.964
I know what
to research now.

00:31.966 --> 00:34.433
I'm going to have to
hand the work off

00:34.435 --> 00:35.801
<i>To someone who</i>
<i>can fight the fight.</i>

00:35.803 --> 00:39.738
You're sterile,
yet engaging in
fertility treatments?

00:39.740 --> 00:40.539
It's not my problem.

00:40.541 --> 00:42.841
Betty:  <i>Last I looked,</i>
<i>your job came with</i>
<i>all the zeroes</i>

00:42.843 --> 00:44.510
<i>On that cheque</i>
<i>my husband wrote.</i>

00:44.512 --> 00:46.745
Elise:  <i>Attention</i>
<i>all hospital staff.</i>

00:46.747 --> 00:47.913
<i>Dr. Austin langham</i>

00:47.915 --> 00:49.515
<i>Has spent the</i>
<i>last two months</i>

00:49.517 --> 00:52.284
<i>Fornicating with</i>
<i>his sister-in-law.</i>

00:52.286 --> 00:54.953
Thought he would
do the trick.
Having our son.

00:54.955 --> 00:57.856
I know my husband
was reticent
about children.

00:57.858 --> 01:00.793
Who ever heard
of a grown man being
afraid of his child?

01:00.795 --> 01:03.462
I think you've misunderstood
what happened between us.

01:03.464 --> 01:05.864
Of course we're not
having an affair, virginia.

01:05.866 --> 01:08.000
We never were.
I'm a happily married man.

01:08.002 --> 01:09.802
Continuing the
work's a good idea,

01:09.804 --> 01:13.772
Only if you
understand the terms.

01:13.774 --> 01:15.441
I agree.

02:01.654 --> 02:04.656
If sex is merely
a vehicle for
procreation,

02:04.658 --> 02:06.191
Then the
end of fertility

02:06.193 --> 02:07.559
Marks the end
of sexual desire.

02:07.561 --> 02:09.595
Yet freud
believed that
menopause

02:09.597 --> 02:11.396
Led to an increase
in female libido.

02:11.398 --> 02:14.566
As usual,
dr. Freud presents
no empirical evidence

02:14.568 --> 02:16.034
To substantiate
his claim.

02:16.036 --> 02:18.337
He wasn't all wrong, though.
The data does show

02:18.339 --> 02:21.974
Certain physiological
changes in women
over 50.

02:21.976 --> 02:24.810
A longer period of foreplay
needed for lubrication,

02:24.812 --> 02:28.514
Fewer vaginal contractions
in the orgasm phase.

02:28.516 --> 02:30.816
When did you see
all these participants?

02:30.818 --> 02:33.385
Oh, those are
only a small sampling.

02:34.654 --> 02:36.522
So you've
resumed the study.

02:36.524 --> 02:37.656
Yes, of course.
Without me.

02:37.658 --> 02:38.690
I did everything
I could, virginia.

02:38.692 --> 02:42.094
The board just wasn't
impressed by
your application.

02:42.462 --> 02:43.629
I don't understand.

02:43.631 --> 02:45.597
Well, try to see it
from their perspective.

02:45.599 --> 02:48.267
Limited experience,
no higher education...

02:48.269 --> 02:49.401
I tried to
go back to school...

02:49.403 --> 02:53.205
You tried,
but didn't see it through.
You chose me instead.

02:53.207 --> 02:53.972
I chose the work.

02:53.974 --> 02:57.009
Virginia, you thought
it was about the work.

02:57.011 --> 02:58.577
I always knew the truth.

02:58.579 --> 03:01.880
That became apparent
on the application, so...

03:01.882 --> 03:06.018
I'm sorry,
but you really only
have yourself to blame.

03:06.020 --> 03:07.152
Because?

03:07.154 --> 03:08.020
For starters?

03:08.022 --> 03:12.090
Under "current
occupation,"
you wrote

03:12.092 --> 03:13.859
"mistress."

03:22.936 --> 03:25.304
Dr. Masters:
You're up.

03:26.906 --> 03:28.273
How long was I...

03:28.275 --> 03:30.008
An hour maybe.
An hour?

03:30.010 --> 03:30.842
Why didn't you
wake me?

03:30.844 --> 03:33.812
You looked like
you needed
the sleep.

03:33.814 --> 03:36.515
Did you know you
sleep with your
mouth open,

03:36.517 --> 03:37.249
Like a baby bird?

03:37.251 --> 03:40.252
We don't sleep here.
Or read.

03:40.254 --> 03:41.753
This isn't a vacation.

03:41.755 --> 03:44.723
I told the sitter
I'd be home
by 10:00.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.525
It's only 9:15. We...

03:46.527 --> 03:47.659
Please get dressed.

03:47.661 --> 03:51.363
You need to
get the study files
out of my trunk.

03:56.703 --> 03:57.836
<i>Oh, goodbye, silky.</i>

03:57.838 --> 04:01.573
<i>And don't wait for me</i>
<i>to write another</i>
<i>story about you.</i>

04:01.575 --> 04:02.908
<i>Drop in any time.</i>

04:02.910 --> 04:05.110
Man:  <i>Goodbye,</i>
<i>mr. Thompson.</i>

04:05.112 --> 04:08.981
<i>Ain't you going to</i>
<i>escort me to the door?</i>

04:09.249 --> 04:10.949
(laughing)

04:15.688 --> 04:19.057
Man: (on tv)  <i>mr. Thompson,</i>
<i>my wife didn't</i>
<i>mean anything.</i>

04:19.059 --> 04:21.460
<i>We've been</i>
<i>married for 25 years.</i>

04:21.462 --> 04:23.395
<i>You're not</i>
<i>going to shoot me.</i>

04:23.397 --> 04:24.396
Mr. Thompson:
<i>Why should I?</i>

04:24.398 --> 04:27.866
<i>If you want</i>
<i>to get out of it,</i>
<i>shoot yourself.</i>

04:46.486 --> 04:47.953
(elevator dings)

04:59.599 --> 05:00.999
(sighs) it's a mess,
but it's all there.

05:01.001 --> 05:05.137
Intake forms,
instrument readings,
sexual histories.

05:05.139 --> 05:06.805
Oh, I could've used these
the other day.

05:06.807 --> 05:11.943
Barbara tried to
make fliers for the study.
Riddled with typos.

05:12.445 --> 05:13.145
Any response yet?

05:13.147 --> 05:14.279
Well, the phone
hasn't stopped
still ringing.

05:14.281 --> 05:18.483
I have seven interviews
with prospective
participants tomorrow,

05:18.485 --> 05:19.151
Six the next day...

05:19.153 --> 05:21.320
I meant any response
from greathouse

05:21.322 --> 05:23.855
About my position
in the study.

05:24.524 --> 05:25.090
Uh...

05:25.092 --> 05:30.262
Why, he can't authorize
me to hire you until
the board signs off.

05:30.264 --> 05:32.597
Has he brought
it up to them?

05:32.599 --> 05:35.067
I'm going to
make sure he does.

05:35.501 --> 05:38.570
Pull your car around
so that we can start
loading these.

05:38.572 --> 05:39.604
Maybe you should
hold on to them.

05:39.606 --> 05:43.442
Someone has to put them
into some kind of order.

05:43.444 --> 05:46.978
I was under the impression,
that someone was
called your secretary.

05:46.980 --> 05:48.046
Oh, barbara can
barely alphabetize.

05:48.048 --> 05:53.018
Besides, you know better
than anyone how all
the pieces fit together.

05:53.086 --> 05:55.253
I want you
to stay connected
to the work.

05:55.255 --> 05:57.856
So I'm not qualified
as a researcher,

05:57.858 --> 06:02.160
But it's fine for me
to play secretary
in my free time?

06:02.162 --> 06:05.597
Virginia, I'm as unhappy
with the situation
as you are.

06:05.599 --> 06:10.035
Are you taking
diet pills?

06:10.037 --> 06:11.036
I'm selling them.

06:11.038 --> 06:12.704
Holding on to
them for a friend?

06:12.706 --> 06:15.140
No. I am selling them.

06:15.142 --> 06:16.675
Without extra money
from the study,

06:16.677 --> 06:18.877
I can barely afford
to pay my rent.

06:18.879 --> 06:21.847
I need to make
a living, bill.

06:40.066 --> 06:43.068
This morning,
we're driving in,

06:43.070 --> 06:44.803
And the parking
attendant says,

06:44.805 --> 06:45.704
"'morning, mrs. Moretti,"

06:45.706 --> 06:50.609
And it takes me
a solid minute to
realize he meant me.

06:50.611 --> 06:54.913
Your whole life you're
walking around
as betty dimello,

06:54.915 --> 06:55.914
The next day,
you're married,

06:55.916 --> 06:58.917
And someone's calling you
some other lady's name.

06:58.919 --> 07:00.652
It's like if,
all of a sudden,

07:00.654 --> 07:04.556
I started calling
you dr. Lipschitz.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.158
Mrs. Moretti.

07:06.160 --> 07:10.195
It makes me feel
like I'm pretending
to be somebody I'm not.

07:10.197 --> 07:12.464
Know what I mean?

07:12.899 --> 07:14.900
(elevator dinging)

07:17.837 --> 07:20.906
Libby: They had
a free subscription offer,
so I figured, why not?

07:20.908 --> 07:24.142
Then I stumbled
upon this article.

07:24.310 --> 07:27.646
Turns out a new baby
is traumatic for a man.

07:27.648 --> 07:31.716
Like his home has been
transformed into
an oversized playpen.

07:31.718 --> 07:35.821
It's messy, it's noisy,
there are smells.

07:35.823 --> 07:38.089
Which explains
why the moment bill
walks in through the door,

07:38.091 --> 07:41.092
The first thing he does
is take out the diaper pail.

07:41.094 --> 07:46.131
It also explains
why bill needs
things calm at home.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.666
Orderly.

07:47.668 --> 07:48.300
Unchanged.

07:48.302 --> 07:53.071
No bottles on the counters.
No pacifiers stuck
between cushions.

07:53.073 --> 07:54.639
It's also
why today
is important.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.741
I mean, I know,
it seems like
a silly luncheon,

07:56.743 --> 08:00.178
But they're
the wives of
bill's new colleagues.

08:00.180 --> 08:02.214
If things go well here,

08:02.216 --> 08:05.016
They report as much
back to their husbands,

08:05.018 --> 08:09.020
And that helps bill at work,
as well as at home.

08:09.822 --> 08:12.190
Is that
a dixie cup on his...

08:12.192 --> 08:15.260
It's a trick I learned
changing my brothers' diapers.

08:15.262 --> 08:17.896
You lose your eyes
if you aren't
careful with boys.

08:17.898 --> 08:19.164
(laughs)

08:19.166 --> 08:21.533
Maybe I should've aksed
before I put it on.

08:21.535 --> 08:23.902
"asked" me
before you put it on.

08:23.904 --> 08:27.105
We talked
about this before,
remember?

08:27.107 --> 08:29.941
Don't worry.
You'll get it.

08:30.810 --> 08:32.577
(cooing)

08:33.613 --> 08:35.247
We should have
a sample pap smear kit

08:35.249 --> 08:37.482
For dr. Papanicolaou
to bring to florida with him.

08:37.484 --> 08:40.552
I put one together
last week.

08:41.420 --> 08:43.154
Several sample kits.

08:43.156 --> 08:45.624
At least three or four.
Even to be safe.

08:45.626 --> 08:48.560
Four seems reasonable,
don't you think?

08:48.562 --> 08:52.264
He's only in st louis once
a year for the conference.

08:52.266 --> 08:55.066
Does he prefer
coffee or tea?

08:55.068 --> 08:55.600
Tea.

08:55.602 --> 08:59.571
With cream and a little...
With the little...

09:00.172 --> 09:02.407
The little squares
of sugar.

09:02.409 --> 09:04.309
Sugar cubes.

09:04.443 --> 09:07.546
You're just
nervous about
tomorrow.

09:07.680 --> 09:10.515
They did name
the pap smear after
dr. Papanicolaou after all.

09:10.517 --> 09:13.218
It makes sense you'd
want to impress him.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.854
I'm not trying
to impress anyone.

09:15.856 --> 09:17.822
Dr. Papanicolaou happens
to be a respected

09:17.824 --> 09:19.958
Figure in the field,
that's all.

09:19.960 --> 09:23.695
His support for
our program would
be enormously useful.

09:23.697 --> 09:28.199
Especially to you.
As you continue
with our work.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.101
Woman: Depaul?

09:30.103 --> 09:31.770
Lillian?

09:39.545 --> 09:41.346
(whispers)
save my seat.

10:23.289 --> 10:25.590
How long have
you worked here?

10:25.958 --> 10:27.692
Three years in March.

10:27.694 --> 10:28.393
I'm over at maternity.

10:28.395 --> 10:31.529
Oh, my girlfriend peg
used to worked there.
How do you like it?

10:31.531 --> 10:35.867
Truthfully,
the stress of
working in a hospital?

10:35.869 --> 10:39.971
Some days, I want to
curl up with a piece
of chocolate cake.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.172
I know what you mean.

10:41.174 --> 10:44.476
We're supposed to
give these to patients
for nausea.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.111
I can imagine it's tough.

10:46.113 --> 10:49.280
Being surrounded by
so much suffering
every day.

10:49.282 --> 10:52.350
Especially when
everyone's so skinny.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.319
I did try
the grapefruit diet.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.321
All it did was
give me cavities.

10:56.323 --> 10:59.090
That is the problem
with fad diets.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.792
They promise
the moon and stars,

11:00.794 --> 11:03.795
But you end up
hungry all the time.

11:04.263 --> 11:07.766
That's why I started
using cal-o-metric.

11:09.101 --> 11:11.670
Dr. Masters:
We'll be following
the same protocol

11:11.672 --> 11:15.206
As in the study
at washington university.

11:15.208 --> 11:17.108
What would
I tell my husband?

11:17.110 --> 11:18.043
What did you say before?

11:18.045 --> 11:20.578
That there
were two doctors,
one of them a lady.

11:20.580 --> 11:23.815
That's the only reason
he let me do it, dr. Masters.

11:23.817 --> 11:28.720
I'm sorry,
but if it's just going
to be you here, alone.

11:28.954 --> 11:32.357
Watching.
I'm sorry.

11:37.229 --> 11:39.531
Part of the study?
Not anymore.

11:39.533 --> 11:41.266
Oh, shame.
Yes.

11:41.268 --> 11:43.168
Without mrs. Johnson,
we can look forward

11:43.170 --> 11:46.171
To more qualified volunteers
declining to participate.

11:46.173 --> 11:49.941
Mrs. Johnson is instrumental
in this part of the process.

11:49.943 --> 11:52.043
No one else puts people
at their ease...

11:52.045 --> 11:53.078
Bill, I get it.

11:53.080 --> 11:55.780
You and I have
been at this
a long time.

11:55.782 --> 11:57.782
You reach a point
in your career,

11:57.784 --> 11:59.317
Same routine day
in and day out,

11:59.319 --> 12:02.787
If you never see
another torn
perineum again,

12:02.789 --> 12:03.588
It'll be too soon.

12:03.590 --> 12:07.959
So you start a sex study,
get a research assistant.

12:07.961 --> 12:10.595
Mrs. Johnson
is indispensable
to this study...

12:10.597 --> 12:13.832
She may seem
indispensable to you,
but to the board?

12:13.834 --> 12:17.035
She's an
overpriced secretary.

12:17.369 --> 12:19.671
Things aren't always
what they seem.

12:19.673 --> 12:21.606
For instance,
barbara doesn't
seem to know

12:21.608 --> 12:23.441
The first thing about
secretarial work.

12:23.443 --> 12:26.978
And yet, apparently,
she's essential.

12:27.379 --> 12:28.913
To you.

12:29.548 --> 12:33.885
I'm simply asking
mrs. Johnson be
brought onto this study

12:33.887 --> 12:36.855
Because she is essential.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.623
To the work.

12:39.792 --> 12:42.594
I'll float the idea
at tomorrow's
board meeting,

12:42.596 --> 12:44.662
See what they think.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.314
(sighs)

13:07.653 --> 13:08.787
What?

13:08.789 --> 13:10.789
They're out of ambrosia?

13:10.890 --> 13:14.325
You know, last year
when you left the study,

13:14.327 --> 13:16.995
I thought to myself, "why?

13:16.997 --> 13:19.264
"why would virginia
leave the work she loves

13:19.266 --> 13:20.498
"to go back to
typing memos?"

13:20.500 --> 13:23.601
And not to mention,
"why would
bill let her go?"

13:23.603 --> 13:25.470
What are you
talking about, austin?

13:25.472 --> 13:29.541
Now I'm thinking,
"what complicates
every relationship?

13:29.543 --> 13:32.544
"what splits
two people up?"

13:34.246 --> 13:34.779
(clears throat)

13:34.781 --> 13:39.651
Um, elise is now
staying at her mother's
across the river. In alton.

13:39.653 --> 13:43.354
When it's my
turn with the kids,
I drive to alton,

13:43.356 --> 13:45.323
Where I pick them up,
then take them

13:45.325 --> 13:50.094
To the chancery
park plaza hotel.

13:50.096 --> 13:52.864
I saw you
there last night.

13:52.866 --> 13:54.766
With bill.

13:55.234 --> 13:57.435
You should have
said something.

13:57.437 --> 14:00.672
We could have
all gotten a drink.

14:02.641 --> 14:07.745
Bill and I have
decided to go ahead
and publish the study.

14:07.747 --> 14:10.481
Now, it's still in
the early stages.

14:10.483 --> 14:14.319
Compiling the data,
drafting the text.

14:14.321 --> 14:16.287
Bill's not welcome
here, obviously.

14:16.289 --> 14:17.922
I'm not welcome
at his hospital.

14:17.924 --> 14:21.259
We can't work
late hours at his house
with the new baby,

14:21.261 --> 14:23.628
And we can't
discuss sex research

14:23.630 --> 14:25.930
At my house,
with my kids there.

14:25.932 --> 14:28.933
So we work
out of the hotel.

14:28.935 --> 14:32.270
Then why did you two
stop working together?

14:33.639 --> 14:37.575
Bill thought we were ready
to present to the faculty.

14:37.577 --> 14:39.344
And I said
we had not
done enough

14:39.346 --> 14:41.679
To prepare them
for what they were
about to hear,

14:41.681 --> 14:46.851
Let alone the sight
of a pulsating vagina
on a projection screen.

14:46.853 --> 14:52.056
We had a terrible fight,
and in the end, I quit.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.559
And after the debacle
of the presentation,

14:54.561 --> 14:56.127
Bill admitted
that he was wrong,

14:56.129 --> 15:00.298
And he apologized,
and he asked me
to come back.

15:00.699 --> 15:01.933
So that's it?

15:01.935 --> 15:04.135
Yes, that's it.

15:05.271 --> 15:07.005
(chuckles)

15:13.279 --> 15:14.312
And we took
the children to see

15:14.314 --> 15:17.181
<i>The music man</i>
with robert preston.
(all gasping)

15:17.183 --> 15:19.651
Oh, I hear
that is fabulous.

15:19.653 --> 15:20.785
It's fabulous.

15:20.787 --> 15:23.388
Oh, I couldn't drag bill
to a broadway musical.

15:23.390 --> 15:26.024
He'd probably
bring a journal
on uterine fibroids

15:26.026 --> 15:29.627
To read during
the slow parts.
(all laughing)

15:29.629 --> 15:31.329
How does he like
the new hospital?

15:31.331 --> 15:33.064
Oh, he couldn't
be happier.

15:33.066 --> 15:37.368
And that study of his?
Is that still happening, too?

15:37.370 --> 15:39.470
I bet you know
all the secrets.

15:39.472 --> 15:41.706
Libby, do tell us
the most delicious thing

15:41.708 --> 15:44.642
You've learned from
all his experiments.

15:44.644 --> 15:48.046
Uh, well, I actually
worked on the study

15:48.048 --> 15:49.747
Myself for a bit,
in his office.

15:49.749 --> 15:53.384
Where I got to see,
first-hand, just how
boring it all is.

15:53.386 --> 15:58.056
The charts and the graphs,
and the incomprehensible
diagram.

15:59.625 --> 16:00.658
(baby cooing)

16:00.660 --> 16:01.893
Someone had
a nice, long nap.

16:01.895 --> 16:09.000
Oh, my goodness, has
that adorable creature been
here this whole time?

16:09.868 --> 16:12.470
He is gorgeous, libby.

16:13.005 --> 16:15.440
And she is so
wonderful with him.

16:15.442 --> 16:17.909
Can I hold?
Mmm-hmm.

16:21.313 --> 16:24.615
