51:35.093 --> 51:36.826
Hating myself
over and over again.

51:36.828 --> 51:40.062
Most people get burned
and don't touch
the stove again.

51:40.064 --> 51:44.733
So what
the hell's wrong with me
that I can't stop touching it?

51:46.069 --> 51:49.105
You don't know
how many times
I've asked myself,

51:49.107 --> 51:52.541
"why can't you
just be more like bill?"

51:53.577 --> 51:56.879
And then the other night

51:58.915 --> 52:01.150
At the hotel,
I realized, I've been

52:01.152 --> 52:03.853
Punishing myself
for no reason.

52:03.855 --> 52:06.188
You and me,
we're the same.

52:06.190 --> 52:08.691
Two men trying our best.

52:08.693 --> 52:10.326
I'm no better or worse
than bill masters.

52:10.328 --> 52:13.028
I thought virginia explained,
we're starting up
the study again.

52:13.030 --> 52:15.598
Come on, bill.
Look who you're
talking to here.

52:15.600 --> 52:18.367
I don't know what
you mean by that.

52:19.069 --> 52:21.537
Just don't do
it the way I did.

52:21.539 --> 52:24.140
You've got to
keep this thing
under wraps.

52:24.142 --> 52:26.275
I'm not the only one
who knows about it.

52:26.277 --> 52:29.879
Lillian depaul
has been wise to it
from the beginning.

52:29.881 --> 52:30.679
And take it from me,

52:30.681 --> 52:35.151
This bachelor life
isn't all it's
cracked up to be.

52:36.653 --> 52:37.386
Don't get me wrong.

52:37.388 --> 52:38.787
There are
some days I feel like,

52:38.789 --> 52:42.191
Literally, I've died
and gone to heaven.

52:42.193 --> 52:43.392
Literally.

52:43.394 --> 52:45.494
But I can't walk by
the nursery anymore.

52:45.496 --> 52:50.065
Because when I do see
those little bundles,

52:51.768 --> 52:56.038
All I can think is
how much I want
to see my kids.

52:56.040 --> 52:57.606
(sighs)

52:57.974 --> 52:59.942
All I'm saying is,

52:59.944 --> 53:02.645
Whatever this is
you have with virginia,

53:02.647 --> 53:08.184
You've got to weigh it
against all of this.

53:12.122 --> 53:14.390
Is it worth it?

53:20.463 --> 53:22.498
(telephone ringing)

53:27.204 --> 53:29.038
(sighs)

53:44.788 --> 53:47.323
Tatti greathouse
just called.

53:47.325 --> 53:51.527
She told me
the most
outlandish story.

53:51.529 --> 53:54.930
She said that
you were fired,

53:54.932 --> 53:58.133
That you assaulted
her husband.

53:58.435 --> 53:59.501
I did lose
my temper, libby.

53:59.503 --> 54:01.770
But you would've, too.
The man is
an utter philistine.

54:01.772 --> 54:05.541
Why do I have to
hear everything
about my husband thirdhand?

54:05.543 --> 54:07.943
I was going to tell you,
but austin was here.

54:07.945 --> 54:11.013
This is the second job
in two months, bill.

54:11.015 --> 54:15.184
Soon there won't be a hospital
left for you to storm out of.

54:15.186 --> 54:18.587
Lib...
Why are you
doing this to me?

54:18.589 --> 54:20.155
Is this our life now?

54:20.157 --> 54:22.124
You going from
one job to another,

54:22.126 --> 54:24.960
Always finding some reason
why it's not good enough?

54:24.962 --> 54:28.464
It's not about
good enough.
It's about...

54:28.466 --> 54:29.298
Your study?

54:29.300 --> 54:32.201
They didn't
understand your study?

54:32.203 --> 54:35.371
They didn't understand it
at maternity either.

54:35.373 --> 54:36.939
That doesn't mean
things won't work out.

54:36.941 --> 54:38.507
They will.
Everything will be fine.

54:38.509 --> 54:42.711
When, bill?
When, exactly,
will everything be fine?

54:42.713 --> 54:46.048
How many more opportunities
do you have to squander

54:46.050 --> 54:48.417
Before you make this work?

54:48.718 --> 54:54.490
You have a wife
and a child who
depend on you.

54:54.791 --> 54:56.659
Doesn't that mean anything?

54:56.661 --> 55:00.696
Yes. Yes, of course.

55:00.698 --> 55:03.465
That's all I think about.

55:04.301 --> 55:06.802
How to do right by you,

55:09.005 --> 55:11.040
The baby.

55:13.743 --> 55:16.945
You just have to
trust me right now.

55:16.947 --> 55:17.613
Okay.

55:17.615 --> 55:21.016
I am going to
take care of you.
Whatever happens.

55:21.018 --> 55:23.018
I will always
take care of you.

55:23.020 --> 55:26.055
You just have
to believe that.

55:26.057 --> 55:30.459
Please, libby.
I just... (stammers)

55:31.061 --> 55:34.330
I need...
All right. All right.

55:35.598 --> 55:38.200
You'll find
the right job.

55:38.401 --> 55:40.569
We'll be okay.

55:41.204 --> 55:43.839
Everything will be okay.

55:55.819 --> 55:58.654
What's six plus
four equal?

55:58.755 --> 56:00.489
Ten.

56:01.491 --> 56:02.758
What's six plus 12?

56:02.760 --> 56:06.261
Your brother can't do
your homework for you.

56:06.263 --> 56:07.262
He does it better, though.

56:07.264 --> 56:09.932
And what happens
when he isn't there, hmm?

56:09.934 --> 56:11.433
When the teacher
calls you in class?

56:11.435 --> 56:13.502
What are you
going to do then?

56:13.903 --> 56:17.072
You can't count
on anybody else
to do your work for you.

56:17.074 --> 56:18.540
You can only
count on yourself.

56:18.542 --> 56:22.311
Everything that's worth doing,
you have to do on your own.

56:22.313 --> 56:24.780
Did you do
everything on your own?

56:25.982 --> 56:27.783
No, I didn't.

56:27.984 --> 56:29.551
But I do now.

56:30.387 --> 56:32.254
From now on.

56:54.911 --> 56:56.011
Man:  <i>We're so very pleased</i>

56:56.013 --> 57:00.416
That you've
decided to join us,
dr. Masters.

57:00.418 --> 57:03.118
The pleasure is all mine.

57:03.286 --> 57:04.286
And I feel comfortable

57:04.288 --> 57:06.588
In speaking
for my partner
when I say

57:06.590 --> 57:08.590
How pleased
we both are

57:08.592 --> 57:13.095
To be bringing our
work here, together.
